The paper discusses the challenges and requirements of fronthaul technology in 5G LTE-U UDCSNet, which involves network infrastructure, communication, and information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses various candidate fronthaul technologies, including optical fiber, millimeter-wave based unlicensed spectrum, Wi-Fi based unlicensed spectrum, sub 6GHz based licensed spectrum, and free-space optical based unlicensed spectrum, which are related to information theory (cs.IT), communication (cs.COMM), and applied physics (cs.AR). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of millimeter-wave technology, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
